The paper deals with AI planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on goal orderings, which is a topic within planning languages and systems (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the complexity of the orderings and their practical relevance, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper proposes a new planning algorithm that could be considered software engineering (cs.SE).
